node.text: Few love stories are as iconic as Elvis and Priscilla Presley's, but it wasn't without its challenges. In the latest issue of PEOPLE, Priscilla opens up about life as the King of Rock and Roll's wife and the constant attention he received from female fans: "Women gravitated to him, so I would be nervous when he had to go places alone. I would even go with him to get his teeth cleaned," she said. "I always had an eye on him because everyone in the world was after him." Tap the bio link for the full story. |📷: Getty
